Place custom fonts in this directory.

The dotfiles configuration assumes Noto Sans and Noto Sans Mono are installed.
Install them via:

  Debian/Ubuntu: sudo apt install fonts-noto fonts-noto-mono
  Arch: sudo pacman -S noto-fonts noto-fonts-emoji
  Fedora: sudo dnf install google-noto-sans-fonts google-noto-sans-mono-fonts

To add custom fonts:
  1. Copy .ttf or .otf files here
  2. Run: mkdir -p ~/.local/share/fonts && cp * ~/.local/share/fonts/ && fc-cache -fv
